senses
  entry
    definition "satisfied or showing satisfaction with things as they are"
    examples ("a contented smile")
    id oewn-00591490-a
    partOfSpeech a
    synonyms (contented)
  entry
    definition "(usually plural) everything that is included in a collection and that is held or included in something"
    examples ("he emptied the contents of his pockets" "the two groups were similar in content")
    id oewn-07971643-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (contents)
  entry
    definition "the state of being contented with your situation in life"
    examples ("he relaxed in sleepy contentedness" "they could read to their heart's content")
    id oewn-14436286-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (contentedness)
  entry
    definition "content communicating a message; what something is about"
    id oewn-06611268-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (message "subject matter" substance)
  entry
    definition "the proportion of a substance that is contained in a mixture or alloy etc."
    id oewn-13838733-n
    partOfSpeech n
  entry
    definition "the amount that can be contained"
    examples ("the gas tank has a capacity of 12 gallons")
    id oewn-13801586-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (capacity)
  entry
    definition "the sum or range of what has been perceived, discovered, or learned"
    id oewn-05817200-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms ("cognitive content" "mental object")
  entry
    definition "something (a person or object or scene) selected by an artist or photographer for graphic representation"
    examples ("a moving picture of a train is more dramatic than a still picture of the same subject")
    id oewn-04354303-n
    partOfSpeech n
    synonyms (subject "depicted object")
  entry
    definition "satisfy in a limited way"
    examples ("He contented himself with one glass of beer per day")
    id oewn-01196771-v
    partOfSpeech v
  entry
    definition "make content"
    examples ("I am contented")
    id oewn-01820811-v
    partOfSpeech v
